## 4. Bug Tracking

Identified Bugs - JJ's User Story
1. createAnnouncement.php threw a fatal PDO error on publish. The INSERT statement referenced announce_deliverytime which did not exist as a column in the Announcement table.
    Resolutuon: Removed announce_deliverytime from the INSERT statement and used created_at and updated_at with NOW() instead to match the actual table schema.
    Severity: High | Fix Status: Fixed
2. index.php threw a fatal PDO error on load. The query referenced expiry instead of the correct column name announce_expiry in the Announcement table.
    Resolution: Updated the query in index.php to use the correct column name announce_expiry along with archived = 0 to filter out archived announcements.
    Severity: High | Fix Status: Fixed
3. The Announcements box on the Department Head homepage was floating alone in the right panel grid instead of appearing below the Compiled Monthly Report.
    Resolution: Moved the Announcements box into the left side grid as a full width row below the Compiled Monthly Report using a spanning class across both columns.
    Severity: Low  | Fix Status: Fixed

Identified bugs - Shannon
1. The event notification pop up on the homepage when not logged in. 
    Resolution: Moved pop-op code block to the top of page.
    Severity: low | Fix Status: Fixed
2. The head dept summary requires ./ for the preview and ../ to open the page.
    Resolution: Changed required_once to include __DIR__ . ‘/../include/db_connect.php’;
    Severity: high | Fix Status: Fixed
